{"run":"opus_round1","family":"v1","meta":{"name":"opus_round1"},"series":{"train":[{"iter":0,"combined_score":0.842304},{"iter":1,"combined_score":0.8230605998628665}],"val":[{"iter":0,"combined_score":0.775926},{"iter":1,"combined_score":0.8021586013559431}]},"full_stats":{"iters":[{"iter":0,"train":0.842304,"val":0.775926},{"iter":1,"train":0.8230605998628665,"val":0.8021586013559431}],"overfit_iters":[],"best_by_val":{"iter":1,"train":0.8230605998628665,"val":0.8021586013559431},"best_by_train":{"iter":0,"train":0.842304,"val":0.775926}},"iters":[{"n":1,"reward":{"status":"EDITED","reward":1,"exit_status":"finished","error":null,"files_changed":["/workspace/harness/system_prompt.md"],"files_added":[],"files_emptied":[],"n_lessons":3},"diff_summary":[{"file":"harness/system_prompt.md","added":47,"removed":0}],"fs_summary":{"files":36,"dirs":13,"bytes":429973},"traj_stats":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","iterations":108,"cost":2.6046575000000005,"wall_sec":2067.36,"exit_status":"finished","success":true,"n_messages":109,"tool_dist":{"Bash":39,"Read":1,"Edit":1,"Write":2},"broker":{"run_harvey_agent":13,"dev_eval":0,"proxy_eval":5,"budget":2,"check_runaway":0,"cost_rank":0},"final_message":"Done. Final state verified \u2014 the committed edit is live in `harness/system_prompt.md`, memory and index written.\n\n## Iteration summary\n\n**Diagnosis (iter0, bare baseline, train mean 0.842).** The headroom is concentrated in **review / \"identify-issues\" / audit / diligence** tasks, which are graded as an `ISSUE_001\u2026N` census. The agent finds the obvious issues but **under-covers** \u2014 it misses issues that need (a) systematic section-by-section coverage and (b) **cross-referencing one document against another** (e.g. a non-compete term vs. an internal *policy cap*; a r\u00e9sum\u00e9 date vs. a PERM requirement). Evidence: employment-labor 0.60 (found its *own* issues, missed the rubric's policy-driven ones), immigration 0.74/0.81 (missed cross-doc date/SOC checks). The bare `system_prompt.md` had **zero task method** \u2014 only workspace/tool conventions. (The env-esg 0.17 \"stuck\" task is a separate *scoping* trap \u2014 it analyzed the wrong property \u2014 which I treated as idiosyncratic, not the generic mode.)\n\n**Change committed (lowest rung, but the gap was a real method gap):** a generic *\"Approach to the work\"* section in `harness/system_prompt.md` \u2014 read all docs fully then fix scope deliberately \u2192 build a **complete issue census** (section-by-section + cross-reference the operative doc against every policy/standard/requirements doc) \u2192 develop each issue fully (cite / why-it-matters / recommendation / classification) \u2192 stay grounded, don't fabricate. **Method, not memorized statutes/numbers.**\n\n**Validation (breadth experiment, candidate vs bare, same proxy grader, 6 diverse tasks):** net mean **0.679 \u2192 0.699 (+0.020), wins 4/6**, with gains exactly where the diagnosis predicted headroom (employment **+0.115**, immigration-compare **+0.070**); the two dips were on already-high tasks within single-seed noise. Turns 15\u201328 vs bare 13\u201328 \u2014 no runaway. Spent ~$12.5 of the $50 experiment cap.\n\n**Carried forward** (`.claude/memory/`): the diagnosis + a flag that prose is now spent on this mode \u2014 if issue-spotting under-coverage persists next iteration, climb to an **enforced, bounded** `agent_loop.py` coverage/cross-reference self-check (hard-capped + `check_runaway`'d) rather than louder prose, and watch already-high tasks for over-coverage regression."}},{"n":2,"reward":{"status":"EDITED","reward":1,"exit_status":"finished","error":null,"files_changed":["/workspace/harness/system_prompt.md"],"files_added":[],"files_emptied":[],"n_lessons":5},"diff_summary":[{"file":"harness/system_prompt.md","added":0,"removed":47}],"fs_summary":{"files":168,"dirs":56,"bytes":2876266},"traj_stats":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","iterations":216,"cost":18.59154775,"wall_sec":8592.35,"exit_status":"finished","success":true,"n_messages":217,"tool_dist":{"Bash":64,"Read":6,"Agent":2,"Write":11,"Edit":1},"broker":{"run_harvey_agent":8,"dev_eval":0,"proxy_eval":0,"budget":19,"check_runaway":2,"cost_rank":0},"final_message":"Iteration complete. Here's what I did and why.\n\n## What I found\nThe inherited harness carried iter1's **\"issue census + cross-reference every doc\"** system-prompt edit, which the 30-task real-grader trend shows is **net-negative** (iter0 bare 0.8423 \u2192 iter1 0.8231, **\u22120.019**). Error analysis on the worst regressions (review-gov \u22120.148, cim \u22120.098, compare-leave \u22120.25) gave a clean, confirmed diagnosis: the regression is **displacement/crowding-out**, not over-coverage \u2014 the census frame makes the agent restructure deliverables around exhaustive taxonomies and **silently evict the foundational \"gimme\" facts** bare stated plainly (cap tables, aggregate figures, \"1x non-participating\", matrix dimensions).\n\n## What I tested (24 paid rollouts, 3 distinct levers, 12-task breadth)\n- **PROSE** (bare + anti-displacement method + numeric discipline): +0.023 proxy across 12 tasks, **but** per-criterion verdicts proved it **breaks strong tasks** (funds 0.947\u21920.842 \u2014 even made 2 figures *worse*; arbitration 0.974\u21920.895) \u2014 iter1's signature, milder.\n- **LOOP** (bare + enforced hard-capped finalize self-check): **\u22120.067** proxy; re-created the displacement on the exact victim tasks. `check_runaway` passed (all <3\u00d7 bare), so it's a quality regression, not a runaway.\n- **Numeric lever is dead**: figures stayed 0\u20131/10 under bare, prose, *and* enforced recompute \u2014 the error is interpretation/inputs, not arithmetic, and \"recompute\" guidance can corrupt correctly-transcribed figures.\n\nThe generalizing obstacle: an **intrinsic asymmetry** \u2014 additive \"do-more\" guidance helps weak tasks (h1b 0.667\u21920.872) but breaks near-complete strong tasks; on a strong-skewed, all-pass eval that nets \u22640. The proxy systematically over-rates elaboration (~+0.04), which is exactly what fooled iter1.\n\n## What I committed\n**Reverted the harness to byte-faithful bare** \u2014 `system_prompt.md` is now byte-identical to the iter0 baseline preamble, `agent_loop.py` is the bare loop, `tools.py` untouched, all compile. This is validated by the strongest possible evidence (the real grader on 30 train tasks: iter0=0.8423 vs the inherited iter1=0.8231), so it's a **~+0.019 real net-positive commit**, not a guess \u2014 and it avoids repeating iter1's now-twice-proven mistake of shipping a proxy-positive/real-negative additive edit.\n\n## Carry-forward leverage\n- `.claude/memory/iter2-additive-method-edits-backfire.md` (the negative-results map), corrected the index, and a `run_harvey_agent`-must-background lesson (I lost $5 to the 10-min Bash cap before adapting).\n- `.claude/tools/proxy_archive_arm.sh` \u2014 reusable A/B harness-variant triage helper.\n\nI stopped at $34.62/$50 spent: the failure pattern is established across 3 levers, so more additive-variant rollouts would be noise-spend, and $15 isn't enough to discover *and* validate a novel safe lever \u2014 better to lock in the validated win than gamble it."}}],"helps_harms":{"tasks":[{"task":"corporate-governance/compare-state-paid-leave-requirements-across-seven-jurisdictions","category":"corporate-governance","bare":0.9666666666666667,"latest":0.7166666666666667,"delta_bare":-0.25,"delta_prev":-0.25,"grades":{"0":0.9666666666666667,"1":0.7166666666666667},"span":0.25,"roll":{"0":"iter0","1":"iter1"},"rolldir":"corporate-governance_compare-state-paid-leave-requirements-across-seven-jurisdictions"},{"task":"corporate-ma/review-governance-diligence/scenario-01","category":"corporate-ma","bare":0.9629629629629629,"latest":0.8148148148148148,"delta_bare":-0.1481,"delta_prev":-0.1481,"grades":{"0":0.9629629629629629,"1":0.8148148148148148},"span":0.1481,"roll":{"0":"iter0","1":"ite